org.quasiliteral.text
Class EYaccFixer

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--org.quasiliteral.text.EYaccFixer
public class EYaccFixer
extends Object

Untamed: Post-processes the output of byacc/Java (Berkeley Yacc for Java) so that it is valid Java.

The problem with byacc/Java's output is simply that it's too large. Specifically, Java turns the table initializers into bytecodes to perform the initialization. These bytecodes exceed Java's limit of 64KB per method. To work around this, EYaccFixer parses the table initializations, serializes the resulting tables into a file to be included as a resource in the e.jar file, and changes the table initializations to initialize these tables by unserializing these resources.

Author:
Mark S. Miller
